-- Czech Republic Won’t Join EU Bank Supervisor, CTK Reports
-- B y   L a d k a   B a u e r o v a
-- 2012-12-13T16:26:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-13/czech-republic-won-t-join-eu-bank-supervisor-ctk-reports.html
The Czech Republic won’t put its
lenders under the direct supervision of the  European Central
Bank , CTK newswire reported, citing Prime Minister Petr Necas.  The Czech Republic, a European Union member, isn’t part of
the 17-nation euro area.  To contact the reporter on this story:
